 and M.F.K. Fisher. Field Days is a heartfelt celebration of the farm-to-table movement and its cultural reverberations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFarm lifexAnecdotesxCaliforniaxSonoma. 0aFarm lifezCaliforniazSonomavAnecdotes. 0aFarmersxBiographyxCaliforniaxSonoma. 0aFarmerszCaliforniazSonomavBiography. 0aOrganic farmingxAnecdotesxCaliforniaxSonoma. 0aOrganic farmingzCaliforniazSonomavAnecdotes. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aamerican food production.  aamerican wine.  acalifornia.  acalifornian wine.  achez panisse.  acultural studies.  adelfina.  adrinking.  aeating.  aenvironmentalism.  afarm to table movement.  afarm workers.  afarmers market.  afarming.  afarmwork.  afood and wine.  afood lovers.  ajack london.  alocal eating.  aluther burbank.  amemoir.  amfk fisher.  anorthern california.  aoak hill farm.  aorganic farming.  asonoma.  astar route farm.  aunited states of america.  avivid reportage.  awhole foods.  awine tasting.  awinemakers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094318640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943186423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943186/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles